    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka: Inflation will peak in September and trend down \u2013 CBSL Governor",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); Sri Lanka's inflation is likely to peak in September 2022, and will trend down afterwards, said Central Bank Chief Dr. Nandalal Weerasinghe on Thursday (18).",
        "He said there will be a gradual increase due to the electricity tariff adjustments, however, inflation would not reach the 70% level as announced before.",
        "\"It will peak around 65% of less than that,\" said the Governor.",
        "In July 2022, Governor Weerasinghe warned that Inflation in Sri Lanka will peak at about 70%.",
        "The Central Bank of Sri Lanka in its Monetary Policy Review No. 6 for 2022, said that the pace of acceleration of inflation has moderated faster than expected.",
        "Headline inflation rose at a slow pace in July 2022, compared to recent months. Such moderation is expected to continue in the period ahead, thereby resulting in a low level of inflation by end 2022, compared to previous projections.",
        "Accordingly, the latest near term forecast of headline inflation shows a faster deceleration, compared to the previous monetary policy review, mainly due to downward revisions to administered prices and their second-round impact, together with the moderation in certain food prices and the stability in the exchange rate. With subdued aggregate demand pressures resulting from tight monetary and fiscal conditions, expected improvements in domestic supply conditions along with the anticipated normalisation in global food and other commodity prices, and the favourable statistical base effect, headline inflation is expected to moderate going forward, and is projected to stabilise in the desired range over the medium term.",
        "Sri Lanka: Inflation will peak in September and trend down \u2013 CBSL Governor",
        "Restructuring domestic debt would lead to an issue \u2013 CBSL Chief",
        "China To Participate In Russia Military Drills, Says India Will Join Too"
      ],
